   <text>
      <body>
         <opener><dateline><date when="1920-08-11">August 11, 1920.</date></dateline>
            <salute>Dear <persName key="hilda_doolittle">Hilda</persName>:</salute></opener>
         <p>I trust this will reach you before you sail. I am not going to write any more now because I have just written you a letter, and I want this to go in the mail at once.</p> 
         <closer>Affectionately yours,</closer>
         
         
         <p>By sales</lb>
            20 <title key="some_imagist_poets">Imagist Poets</title>, 1915    .46 2/3     $9.33</lb>
            23      "       "           "        .58 1/3        13.42</lb>
            13      "       "         1916    .46 2/3          6.07</lb>
            17      "       "           "         .58 1/3          9.92</lb>
            19      "       "         1917    .46 2/3       8.87</lb>
            21      "       "           "        .58 1/3     12.25 </lb>
            59.86</lb>
         One sixth of $59.86 is <measure type="currency" num="$9.97">$9.97</measure></p>
         <p>Miss <persName key="amy_lowell">Lowell</persName> was obliged to leave 
         before this letter could be signed</p>
